---
description: Git and version control rules — automatically applied when editing git-related files
globs: [".github/**", "*.md", "CHANGELOG*"]
alwaysApply: false
---

For commit, branch, or pull-request tasks, read `rules/version-control.md` before proceeding.

Key constraint: commit message format is `<type>(<module>): <short description>`.

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`.

Example: `feat(hostapp-backend): add audit trail endpoint`
